Dancer-Logger-Pipe

NAME
       Dancer::Logger::Pipe - pipe-based logging engine for Dancer

VERSION
       Version 0.01

SYNOPSIS
       Used to pipe the logs from Dancer. This requires some additional settings.

         logger: pipe
         pipe:
           command:     "/usr/bin/cronolog /var/log/dancer/%Y/%m/%d/dancer.log"

DESCRIPTION
       This is a pipe-based logging engine that allows you to pipe your log output

INSTALLATION

To install this module, run the following commands:

	perl Makefile.PL
	make
	make test
	make install

SUPPORT AND DOCUMENTATION

After installing, you can find documentation for this module with the
perldoc command.

    perldoc Dancer::Logger::Pipe

You can also look for information at:

    RT, CPAN's request tracker
        http://rt.cpan.org/NoAuth/Bugs.html?Dist=Dancer-Logger-Pipe

    AnnoCPAN, Annotated CPAN documentation
        http://annocpan.org/dist/Dancer-Logger-Pipe

    CPAN Ratings
        http://cpanratings.perl.org/d/Dancer-Logger-Pipe

    Search CPAN
        http://search.cpan.org/dist/Dancer-Logger-Pipe/


